-- Factorial says insider trading allegations in India "without merit"
-- 
-- Fri Jun 06, 2014 03:34AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, June 6 (Reuters) - Hong Kong-based hedge fund Factorial Capital Management said insider trading allegations against the firm by India's market regulator are "without merit" and the hedge fund will fully c-operate in the investigation.

The Securities Exchange Board of India (SEBI) on Thursday accused Factorial of insider trading, saying it suspected the hedge fund had shorted L&T Finance Holdings Ltd <LTFH.NS> before the announcement of a share sale in mid-March. [ID:nL3N0ON0FW] "Factorial believes that the allegations outlined in an interim order from the Indian regulator (SEBI) are without merit," the hedge fund firm said in a statement to Reuters.